She was exposed to two patients who had COVID on 8/13/22 and 8/15/22. Her last date worked was 8/15/22 but did not test positive until 8/25/22. That is why the employer shows a date of injury of 8/25/22. BWC's web site would not allow the date of injury to be after the last date worked. With COVID exposure, medical protocol requires them to stop working but they may not test positive until after the last date they worked.
